Police spokesman Captain Nqobile Gwala said the team acted on information received by crime intelligence.Police worked together with Home Affairs officials and the Durban public order police to conduct a search at the Silverglen factory which employs over 300 people."Officials discovered that 35 employees didn't possess any work permits and were also in the country illegally. All 35 were placed under arrest most of them were from Lesotho and Malawi " she said.Gwala said the owner was aware that the workers were in the country illegally.He has also been arrested and will face charges of employing illegal immigrants.They're expected to appear in the Chatsworth Magistrate's Court on Thursday morning.-TMG Digital/TimesLIVE